attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, Intel 80386, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The ELF binary demonstrates multiple behaviors typical of Linux botnets or backdoors. Key malicious indicators include: XOR-based string deobfuscation (sub_804911a), manual daemonization through setsid and redirection of standard streams to /dev/null (sub_8059847), and system fingerprinting via /proc/cpuinfo and /proc/stat. The presence of a massive quantity of obfuscated strings and the implementation of custom runtime decryption routines are consistent with malware families such as Mirai or Gafgyt.
